<div id="review_3498679544" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3498679544" />
    <a title="Michael David" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43787758-michael-david"><img alt="Michael David" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1588459700p2/43787758.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3498679544?book_show_action=true">Aug 16, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael David" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael David" href="/user/show/43787758-michael-david">Michael David</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3498679544" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1390133989642685146">Rex and Saskia, a couple, are on a road trip in France. After stopping at a gas station, Saskia goes inside to get drinks while Rex fills the tank. Saskia is never seen again. She seems to have vanished into thin air. Eight years later, Rex (now in a relationship with Lieneke) still can‚Äôt help but wonder what happened to Saskia. After relaunching a public campaign into her disappearance, Saskia‚Äôs kidnapper reaches out to Rex. He will reveal everything that happened to Saskia...as long as Rex goe</span>
  <span id="freeText1390133989642685146" style="display:none">Rex and Saskia, a couple, are on a road trip in France. After stopping at a gas station, Saskia goes inside to get drinks while Rex fills the tank. Saskia is never seen again. She seems to have vanished into thin air. Eight years later, Rex (now in a relationship with Lieneke) still can‚Äôt help but wonder what happened to Saskia. After relaunching a public campaign into her disappearance, Saskia‚Äôs kidnapper reaches out to Rex. He will reveal everything that happened to Saskia...as long as Rex goes through the exact same process. <br /><br />‚ÄúObsession is the ultimate weapon.‚Äù - Tagline for the 1993 film remake. <br /><br />THE VANISHING is a Dutch thriller, translated to English. It was adapted into a film in 1988, and then remade in America in 1993. The American remake is one of my favorite ‚Äúclassic‚Äù movies. It stars Kiefer Sutherland and Sandra Bullock as the young couple, and Jeff Bridges as the villain. Many fans of this novel prefer the original film as well, and were not happy with the ending of the American remake. This ending is dark, disturbing, and horrifying. I‚Äôve had nightmares about it on and off over the years. The remake adds a bit more to the climax, and even though it‚Äôs still disturbing and horrifying, it didn‚Äôt work for most audiences. I guess I‚Äôm in the minority. I found the original film quite cheesy until the ending. <br /><br />As for the book...I‚Äôve had a copy of this for years, and am glad I finally got around to it. The beginning and ending are gripping, but there are some sections in the middle that could‚Äôve been taken out. I didn‚Äôt need to read 5 pages about a badminton game. The translation is a bit clunky as well. I‚Äôm still glad to have finally read the book that inspired the films. <br /><br />My personal opinion: Skip this book and skip the 1988 film. Watch the 1993 film remake, and then google the ending of this book or the 1988 version to see the differences.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1390133989642685146" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
