        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer881426953" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16150518530155392497">I haven&apos;t read many books as terrifying as this one, particularly one so short!<br/><br/>Rex and Saskia are a young Dutch couple on a road trip in France, one evening they stop off at a gas station to rest and Saskia disappears without any trace. We jump forward eight years where we find Rex trying to move on with his life. He has a new fianc√© and things seem to be going well however it soon becomes apparent he is suffering from some kind of post-traumatic stress and still hasn&apos;t recovered from his experi</span>
  <span id="freeText16150518530155392497" style="display:none">I haven't read many books as terrifying as this one, particularly one so short!<br /><br />Rex and Saskia are a young Dutch couple on a road trip in France, one evening they stop off at a gas station to rest and Saskia disappears without any trace. We jump forward eight years where we find Rex trying to move on with his life. He has a new fianc√© and things seem to be going well however it soon becomes apparent he is suffering from some kind of post-traumatic stress and still hasn't recovered from his experience.<br /><br />The story is original and very tense, I was on the edge of my seat more than once. Due to its very short length the story moves along at a lovely pace and doesn't fall into the trap of drowning the reader with too much detail. The characters seem genuine and likeable.<br /><br />By the end of the book my blood had been chilled several times and i've still got the book on my mind three days later<br /><br />The book has been adapted to film twice, once in Holland (1988) and again in the US (1993) I haven't seen either of these films but will keep an eye open<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16150518530155392497" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
